Subject: Portcullis Security Advisory 05-004


Portcullis Security Advisory
 
Vulnerable System: 
 
MediaPartner 5.0
 
Vulnerability Title:  
 
Source Code Disclosure
 
Vulnerability discovery and development: 
 
Portcullis Security Testing Service
 
Affected systems: 
 
Emotion MediaPartner Web Server Version 5.0 and 5.1
 
Details:
 
By appending a period ('.') or a plus-sign ('+') to a request for a
.bhtml file, the source of the .bhtml file is returned rather than
.executed.
 
Impact:
 
Allows an attacker to determine how the application works and can
aid in further attacks.  Note this vulnerability was used to
discover "Password Update Process Flaw" vulnerability.
 
 
Exploit:
 
No exploit required. Example: http://target_ip/login.bhtml.
 
 
